longBusinessSummary: Grupo MÃ©xico, S.A.B. de C.V. engages in copper production, rail transportation, and infrastructure businesses worldwide. The company operates through Mining, transportation, and Infrastructure divisions. The Mining division explores for, exploits, and obtains minerals, metals, and other byproducts, including copper, silver, molybdenum, zinc, sulfuric acid, gold, and selenium. It owns interests in 15 underground and open pit mines, and 13 exploration projects in Mexico, Peru, the United States, Chile, Ecuador, and Spain. The Transportation division offers railroad transportation services, including general hauling and intermodal services by railroad; passenger transportation services; and auxiliary terminal management and intra-terminal hauling services. This division provides railroad services for the farming, automotive, cement, energy, intermodal, metals and minerals, industrial products, and chemical and fertilizer sectors. It operates a railroad network of 10,570 km across 24 states in Mexico. The Infrastructure division offers land and marine drilling services, such as the leasing and operation of oil rigs; and engineering services. It also generates energy through a combined cycle plant and wind farm; and constructs and operates Salamanca-LeÃ³n highway. Grupo MÃ©xico, S.A.B. de C.V. was founded in 1942 and is based in Mexico City, Mexico.
